Package net.co.java.packets

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    PacketHandler
    A PacketHandler is a PacketWrapper that implements the way the GameServer should handle the IncomingPacket
    PacketWrapper
    A PacketWrapper wraps an IncomingPacket and provides additional getters (and optional setters for bi-directional packets) for the packet attributes.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Character_Creation_Packet  
    GeneralData
    The General Data packet performs a variety of tasks for the client, these vary from moving the client around the game, to ending an XP skill.
    IncomingPacket
    A wrapper providing methods to read unsigned values from the byte array from the Sockets' InputStream.
    InteractPacket
    The Interact packet is most commonly used for direct melee/archer attacks, but also used for certain player to player actions, such as marriage.
    ItemUsage
    Item usage packet
    MessagePacket
    This packet is used to send messages to other players and to instruct the client on what errors to display on login.
    PacketWriter  
    UpdatePacket
    The Entity Status packet, also known as the "Update packet" is used to change the appearance(in some cases), certain values unique to a character (such as level, stat points, exp) and show active abilities (in other cases).
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    GeneralData.SubType
    Enumeration for the subtypes
    InteractPacket.Mode
    An enumeration of Interaction modes
    ItemUsage.Mode
    Enumeration of Item usage modes
    MessagePacket.MessageType
    An enumeration of various Message Types for the MessagePackets
    PacketType
    Enumeration for the Packet types
    UpdatePacket.Mode
